-1.title: Episode dated 2 April 2017
-1.plot:
Know what this is about?
 Be the first one to add a plot.

1.title: The Simpsons
1.plot: Bakers compete to see whose creation is worthy to appear at a bash, in honor of The Simpsons (1989).

2.title: DC Comics
2.plot: Bakers compete to have their creation featured at a DC Comics celebration.

3.title: The Knot
3.plot: A cake for a couple's dream wedding is needed.

4.title: Nintendo
4.plot: A Nintendo challenge features cakes inspired by the video game, Super Mario Bros.

5.title: Hello Kitty
5.plot: Winning baker's cake will be featured at the launch of Hello Kitty's North American tour.

6.title: LEGO
6.plot: Four bakers piece together LEGO-themed cake creations. Michael McNally is the guest judge.

7.title: The Sound of Music
7.plot: The cake artists celebrate the 50th anniversary of the movie, The Sound of Music (1965).

8.title: Girl Scouts
8.plot: Four cake artists compete to have their creation featured at a celebration for the Girl Scouts of America, in the Season 1 finale.

1.title: Christmas: Ultimate Christmas Lights
1.plot: Seven teams of culinary artists compete to create over-the-top holiday cake displays, beginning with a challenge based on the Frozen (2013) character, "Olaf". Later, Christmas lights, that are eye-popping and edible, are presented to the judges.

2.title: Christmas: Who's Coming Down the Chimney?
2.plot: The six remaining teams take part in a challenge, inspired by ugly Christmas sweaters. Later, they create displays that imagine who's coming down the chimney, when Santa takes a sick day.

3.title: Christmas: Santa's New Ride
3.plot: The five remaining teams creative imaginative edible toys made by Santa's unsupervised elves. Also: they construct a new ride for the man in red.

4.title: Christmas: Holiday Song
4.plot: Four teams remain to compete in challenges, which include imagining Santa in space and bringing popular Christmas songs to life.

5.title: Christmas: Charlie Brown Celebrates
5.plot: Three teams remain to compete in challenges that commemorates the 50th anniversary of A Charlie Brown Christmas (1965). Included: Snoopy's dog house is decked out for the holidays; and preparations are made for the ultimate Peanuts bash.

6.title: Christmas: Ultimate Gingerbread House
6.plot: Actress Monica Potter helps determine the winner, when the final two teams are tasked with creating edible snow globes and the ultimate gingerbread house.

1.title: Star Wars
1.plot: In the Season 3 premiere, bakers compete to have their cakes, front and center, at a celebration of the release of a "Star Wars" video game.

2.title: Dr. Seuss
2.plot: A Dr. Seuss celebration in honor of the book, "What Pet Should I Get?".

3.title: Kung Fu Panda 3
3.plot: The directors of Kung Fu Panda 3 (2016) help decide which competing baker's cake will be featured at a massive party celebrating the movie's release.

4.title: Minecraft
4.plot: A Minecraft cake is needed for a party, celebrating the video game.

5.title: Valentine's Day
5.plot: The competing bakers work with expert chocolatiers to make a centerpiece for a romantic Valentine's Day wine-tasting event.

6.title: Shark Lagoon
6.plot: As the world-famous Aquarium of the Pacific throws a massive celebration for their Shark Lagoon nights, four bakers will take a bite at the chance to make a jaw-dropping cake centerpiece. Guest judge is Luke Richmond.

7.title: Shrek
7.plot: A cake celebrating the 15th anniversary of the movie, Shrek (2001), is needed for a party.

8.title: Party Animals
8.plot: The bakers help celebrate a baby hippo named Rosie's first birthday, when they compete to have their cake served at a wild party being thrown by the Los Angeles Zoo.

9.title: Sesame Street
9.plot: Big Bird and the whole Sesame Street (1969) gang appear, as four talented bakers compete to have their creation at the center of a party celebrating the show's newest season. Cookie Monster and executive producer Carol-Lynn Parente help choose a winner.

10.title: Willy Wonka
10.plot: The 45th anniversary of the film, Willy Wonka & the Chocolate Factory (1971), is celebrated by the bakers as they compete to have their cake creation on display at an epic party. Helping choose the winner is actor Paris Themmen, who played the role of "Mike Teevee" in the 1971 movie.

11.title: Archie
11.plot: Creation of a cake for the celebration of 75 years of the "Archie" comic book.

12.title: Dinosaurs
12.plot: Four bakers capture dinosaurs in cake form, for the chance to have their creation featured at a party and win the prize of $10,000.

13.title: Alice in Wonderland
13.plot: In the Season 3 finale, four amazing bakers put their skills to the test and take on "Alice in Wonderland" for a prize worth $10,000 and the chance for their creations to be featured at a 65th anniversary celebration of the classic Disney animated film, Alice in Wonderland (1951).

1.title: Captain America
1.plot: In the Season 4 premiere, cakes in celebration of the 75th birthday of Captain America are created.

2.title: SpongeBob
2.plot: Cakes celebrating SpongeBob SquarePants are created by four competing bakers.

3.title: Charlie Brown's All-Stars
3.plot: Competing bakers try to impress guest judge Lindsay Schulz, granddaughter of Peanuts creator Charles Schulz, when they make cakes to celebrate the 50th anniversary of the Charlie Brown's All Stars! (1966) animated TV special.

4.title: How to Train Your Dragon
4.plot: Cakes are created in hopes they'll be chosen to be displayed at a party celebrating "How to Train Your Dragon".

5.title: Emoji
5.plot: Cakes celebrating emojis are created by the competing artists.

6.title: Cobra's Curse
6.plot: Ancient Egypt inspires the bakers when they create cakes for a party celebrating the grand opening of the thrill ride, Cobra's Curse, at Busch Gardens Tampa Bay.

7.title: Beauty & the Beast
7.plot: The film, Beauty and the Beast (1991), is the theme when four bakers compete to have their creations as the centerpiece of a party, celebrating the iconic movie's 25th anniversary. Included: Paige O'Hara, the voice of Belle, is a guest judge.

8.title: Halo
8.plot: Bakers enter the world of gaming, when they compete to have their creations featured at the Halo World Championship.

9.title: Madeline
9.plot: The adorable Parisian adventurer, Madeline, is celebrated when four bakers compete to have their creations featured at a party honoring the beloved children's book character.

10.title: Jelly Belly
10.plot: The prize for the winning baker is to have their cake featured at a party celebrating Jelly Belly.

11.title: Paddington
11.plot: The 90th birthday of Paddington the Bear creator Michael Bond is celebrated, when the four competing bakers create special cakes for the occasion.

12.title: Where's Waldo
12.plot: Season 4 comes to a close with cakes being made for a party celebrating "Where's Waldo?".

13.title: Garfield
13.plot: Cakes, celebrating the cat Garfield, are created for a special party.

14.title: Powerpuff Girls
14.plot: Bakers compete to have their cakes, celebrating "The Powerpuff Girls", chosen by the judges, who include the voice actresses who play Blossom, Bubbles and Buttercup on the animated series.

15.title: Wonder Woman
15.plot: The 75th anniversary of Wonder Woman is celebrated with cakes, created in hopes of being chosen to be featured as the centerpiece at a party in the hero's honor.

17.title: The Addams Family
17.plot: Cakes that are a little creepy and kooky are created for an Addams Family challenge.

18.title: Magic
18.plot: Magician Mat Franco is on hand to help choose the baker, who will have their cake appear at a party celebrating tricks and illusions.

19.title: Trolls
19.plot: Bakers compete to have their creations featured at the center of a release party for the DreamWorks animated movie, Trolls (2016).

20.title: Transformers
20.plot: Four talented bakers compete to take home $10,000, by making Transformers-themed cakes; Simon Waters, senior vice-president of global brand licensing for Hasbro, takes a seat on the judging panel.

21.title: Rugrats
21.plot: Four bakers battle it out for the chance to have their cake as the centerpiece of a party celebrating the Rugrats (1990) TV show. Elizabeth Daily, the voice actress behind the animated series' Tommy Pickles, helps determine the winner.

22.title: Space Jam
22.plot: Cake Wars celebrate the 20th anniversary of Space Jam (1996); four bakers compete for their cake to be the centerpiece of the celebration; Bill Farmer, the voice actor behind Sylvester and Yosemite Sam, acts as a guest judge.

23.title: Rose Bowl
23.plot: Cake Wars celebrates the long-standing tradition of the Rose Bowl college football game; former NFL player and Rose Bowl champion Lawrence Jackson is a judge.

24.title: Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles
24.plot: Four master bakers compete to take home $10,000 and have their cake showcased at a celebration of the Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles; Greg Cipes and Mae Whitman, voices of Michelangelo and April O'Neil, act as guest judges.

25.title: Happy Feet
25.plot: Cake Wars (2015) celebrates the animated film, Happy Feet (2006); four bakers compete to have their cakes displayed at the Aquarium of the Pacific; Luke Richmond, from the Aquarium of the Pacific, joins the judges panel.

26.title: Monopoly
26.plot: Cake Wars (2015) celebrates the iconic board game, Monopoly; four bakers compete for their cakes to be the centerpiece at a party celebrating Monopoly; Rebecca Hollander, director of the Monopoly brand at Hasbro, helps choose the winner.

27.title: Roald Dahl
27.plot: Beloved stories, "James and the Giant Peach", "Charlie and the Chocolate Factory" and "The BFG", come to the kitchen to celebrate the 100th birthday of children's author Roald Dahl; special guest judge is Chloe Dahl, Roald Dahl's granddaughter.

1.title: Christmas: Santa's Makeover
1.plot: Seven teams, composed of a cake artist, sugar sculptor, and master food carver, compete; they must tackle the worst gift under the Christmas tree; giving Santa Claus a makeover.

2.title: Christmas: How the Grinch Stole Christmas
2.plot: The six remaining trios celebrate the 50th anniversary of How the Grinch Stole Christmas! (1966); a modern twist on "How the Grinch Stole Christmas"; the teams add holiday spirit to the Grinch's tale; Dr. Seuss Enterprises president Susan Brandt join the judges panel.

3.title: Christmas: The Nutcracker
3.plot: Five remaining teams are challenged to show how Santa's elves get in shape; teams then must give the Nutcracker a modern twist; Charles Phoenix and Sherry Yard, along with special guest judge Tamera Mowry-Housley, determine which team is eliminated.

4.title: Christmas: Animals Celebrate Christmas Too
4.plot: Four remaining teams of a master cake artist, sugar sculptor and food carver return to battle; the contestants must imagine Santa's undercover disguise; the contestants create a delicious forest world, where the animals celebrate Christmas.

5.title: Christmas: Santa's Workshop
5.plot: The final three teams must help Santa with a gift for Mrs. Claus; the teams create the ultimate Santa's Workshop; guest judge and candy queen Jackie Sorkin helps to determine which teams will face off in the next round.

6.title: Christmas: Ultimate Christmas Front Yard
6.plot: The epic final battle of Cake Wars: Christmas; the final two teams must create an edible Rudolph Christmas card; in the final round, the teams must create the ultimate Christmas-decorated yard.

7.title: Champs: Happy Birthday, Dr. Seuss!
7.plot: Four returning Cake Wars champions compete for their cake to be the centerpiece of Dr. Seuss birthday party; Susan Brandt, president of Dr. Seuss Enterprises, guest judges.

8.title: Champs: The Avengers
8.plot: Four champion cake artists make Avengers cakes for the chance to win $10,000; Stephen Wacker, VP of Animation, Development and Current Series at Marvel Enterprises, serves as a guest judge.

9.title: Champs: Shrek
9.plot: Four returning champions do battle for the chance to have their cake as the centerpiece of a party celebrating the 10th anniversary of Shrek the Third (2007); only one will remain undefeated and take home $10,000.

10.title: Champs: Lego
10.plot: Four champions return and compete to have their cake displayed as the centerpiece of a LEGO party; Amanda Santoro from LEGO serves as guest judge.

11.title: Champs: Pokemon
11.plot: The champion bakers battle for their cake to be the centerpiece of a party celebrating Pikachu and the rest of Pokémon.

12.title: Saban's Power Rangers
12.plot: Four master bakers create cakes inspired by Saban's Power Rangers and compete to win the chance to display it at a party celebrating the movie, Power Rangers (2017), and take home $10,000; the Yellow Ranger herself, singer and actress Becky G, serves as guest judge.

13.title: Champs: Disney Princesses
13.plot: It's an adventure for the ages with Cinderella, Ariel, Princess Jasmine, and many more, as four champion bakers battle to have their cakes serve as the centerpiece of a party celebrating Disney's Princesses.

14.title: Smurfs: The Lost Village
14.plot: Four talented cake artists battle for the chance to have their cake as the centerpiece of a party celebrating the animated movie, Smurfs: The Lost Village (2017); Kelly Asbury, director of the film, joins the judging panel.

imdb.title: Cake Wars
plot: Bakers compete to have their cakes showcased at a major party or special event.::anonymous
